they're starting to assign
the videos instead of

00:23:39.840 --> 00:23:41.218
reading and homework and then you do your

00:23:41.218 --> 00:23:42.340
homework in class.

00:23:42.340 --> 00:23:44.036
That's where you really benefit from;

00:23:44.036 --> 00:23:45.670
one, having the teacher there, even more,

00:23:45.670 --> 00:23:46.637
having your peers there.

00:23:46.637 --> 00:23:50.923
Jon: Exactly. I think that
will be really fruitful.

00:23:50.923 --> 00:23:54.332
Something else that I'm interested in is

00:23:54.332 --> 00:23:56.531
the notion that you
talked about caring about

00:23:56.531 --> 00:24:00.153
the intuition and
transmitting the intuition ...

00:24:00.153 --> 00:24:04.227
That happens in a pretty
personal way for you,

00:24:04.227 --> 00:24:08.387
so what we get is this
view through your eyes

00:24:08.387 --> 00:24:11.427
of how these intuitions made sense to you,

00:24:11.427 --> 00:24:14.934
which is great because a lot of times that

00:24:14.934 --> 00:24:17.055
doesn't come front and center.

00:24:17.055 --> 00:24:20.333
If we start to get a
few more people like you

00:24:20.333 --> 00:24:23.133
out there as well and we
can start to triangulate

00:24:23.133 --> 00:24:25.967
on these things, it'll
be even better because

00:24:25.967 --> 00:24:30.135
ultimately, there might
be some other person

00:24:30.135 --> 00:24:32.433
like you might have a
way of thinking about it

00:24:32.433 --> 00:24:34.138
that works better for me ...

00:24:34.138 --> 00:24:34.820
Sal: Absolutely.

00:24:34.820 --> 00:24:36.473
Jon: And if I could
access the context of a

00:24:36.473 --> 00:24:41.231
particular subject, if
